  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are international laws and agreements designed to combat money laundering. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) is the primary international organization that sets standards and promotes effective implementation of legal, regulatory, and operational measures to combat money laundering. Many countries have implemented anti-money laundering (AML) laws based on FATF recommendations, including:\n\n1. Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious activities\n2. Implementing customer identification procedures\n3. Maintaining financial transaction records\n4. Cooperating in international investigations\n5. Imposing penalties for money laundering offenses\n\nThe United Nations and International Monetary Fund also support global efforts to prevent money laundering through various conventions and guidelines.",
